      "description": "Presenting a collector-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, finished in its original Montego Blue Mica. This example retains its factory-spec 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary powerplant, delivering linear boost through the original 5-speed manual transaxle. The chassis remains structurally flawless, featuring the R1-specific dual oil coolers and a Torsen limited-slip differential. Recent service includes a full cooling system overhaul and a compression test yielding exceptional results across all rotor faces. With its 50/50 weight distribution and sophisticated four-wheel double-wishbone suspension, this FD offers an unfiltered analog driving experience. The interior is immaculate, showcasing original bolstered buckets and a crack-free dashboard. A rare opportunity to acquire a mechanically pristine, unmodified icon of the Golden Era.",
